From 5d3d9dfee75efd1163150705818d735cad837525 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: "Ryan X. Charles" <ryan@ryanxcharles.com>
Date: Thu, 28 May 2026 19:51:12 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 07/10] Enable Mojo JS on PDF viewer frame
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The viewer's bindings cried for Mojo's name,
a subframe spurned by the main-frame gate's domain.
A broker, empty, logging what it's asked,
unmasks the global, lets init be unmasked.
The viewer woke, built its plugin with pride—
then IsPdfRenderer slammed the door from inside.
